# CODEOWNERS — drop-in template aligned with the agents-md standard.
#
# Copy to your repo root as `CODEOWNERS` (or `.github/CODEOWNERS` /
# `docs/CODEOWNERS`) and replace @team-* / @<user> placeholders with
# the actual teams in your GitHub org.
#
# Rules of thumb:
#   - High-blast-radius paths get TWO owners.
#   - Owners are *teams* where possible, not individuals.
#   - `*` at top is a sane default; later rules override per-path.
#   - Update this file via PR like any other code change.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default — any file not matched by a later rule.
* @org/default-reviewers

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Database / migrations — direct connection touched here.
/prisma/                              @org/platform @org/dba
/drizzle/                             @org/platform @org/dba
/migrations/                          @org/platform @org/dba

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth, IAM, sessions.
/lib/auth/                            @org/security
/middleware/auth/                     @org/security
/app/api/auth/                        @org/security

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CI / workflows — accidental changes here are expensive.
/.github/workflows/                   @org/platform
/scripts/                             @org/platform
/scripts/deploy/                      @org/platform @org/sre

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Payment / billing.
/lib/billing/                         @org/finance @org/platform
/app/api/billing/                     @org/finance @org/platform

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Prompts + evals — code review + LLM domain review.
/prompts/                             @org/llm @org/product
/evals/                               @org/llm @org/product

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secrets / config schema.
/.env.example                         @org/security
/config/                              @org/platform

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The spec itself, if you vendor agents-md into your repo.
/CLAUDE.md                            @org/maintainers
/AGENTS.md                            @org/maintainers
/docs/agents-md/                      @org/maintainers
